Primary rib tumors in 54 dogs.

Pirkey-Ehrhart N, Withrow SJ, Straw RC, Ehrhart EJ, Page RL, Hottinger HL, Hahn 
KA, Morrison WB, Albrecht MR, Hedlund CS, et al.

Fifty-four dogs with primary tumors of the rib were evaluated. Thirty-four dogs 
had osteosarcomas, 15 dogs had chondrosarcomas, three dogs had hemangiosarcomas, 
and two dogs had fibrosarcomas. Forty-nine dogs had en bloc excision. Within the 
osteosarcoma group, nine animals received postoperative adjuvant chemotherapy. 
These animals had significantly longer median disease-free intervals (225 days) 
and median survival times (240 days) than dogs with osteosarcoma treated by 
