were significantly more than the total ablation charges (p < 0.001). This study 
suggests that radiofrequency catheter ablation is of clinical benefit in 
treating paroxysmal supraventricular tachycardia, and markedly reduces the cost 
of definitive therapy. This strategy appears to be more economical than 
pharmacologic treatment.

